In this letter, President Barack Obama notifies the Speaker of the House and the President Pro Tempore of the Senate about the deployment of additional U.S. Armed Forces personnel to South Sudan. The deployment is in response to the security situation in South Sudan and is meant to support the security of U.S. personnel and the U.S. Embassy in Juba. Additional forces are also being pre-positioned in Uganda to support the security of U.S. citizens and property in South Sudan. The exact scope and duration of the deployments are unknown at this time. The President states that he has ordered this action to protect U.S. citizens and in line with his constitutional authority as Commander in Chief and Chief Executive. The President provides this report to Congress as part of his efforts to keep them fully informed, in accordance with the War Powers Resolution.